  "conclusion": "Yes. The father’s oral promise is enforceable because it is supported by consideration and is not barred by the Statute of Frauds (it is performable within one year, and the main purpose exception likely removes it from the suretyship writing requirement), and the father’s mistaken belief about tax deductions does not excuse performance absent an express condition or other defense."
