iting.\n\nMistake: The father’s later discovery that no tax deduction was available is a unilateral mistake about a collateral consequence. That mistake generally does not excuse performance and does not negate assent, absent fraud or an agreement making the deduction a condition of the promise. No such condition is stated.",
